  <div class="container breadcrumbs">
   <h1>
    NextBUZZ – A Bus-Headway Controller
   </h1>
   <p>
    A software system to coördinate buses on a route, based on an idea by
    <a href="http://www2.isye.gatech.edu/~jjb/" target="_blank">
     John J. Bartholdi III
    </a>
    and
    <a href="http://www.chicagobooth.edu/faculty/directory/e/donald-d-eisenstein" target="_blank">
     Donald D. Eisenstein
    </a>
    .
				The software for project was designed and largely written by Loren K. Platzman.
			Implementation was led by
    <a href="http://www.cc.gatech.edu/fac/Russell.Clark/">
     Russ Clark
    </a>
    , Jin Lee, and David Williamson.
   </p>
   <p>
    In partnership with Georgia Tech Parking and Transportation Services, NextBuzz was implemented in 2013 to adjust vehicle layover time based on real-time data. The system decreased vehicle headway and reduced wait times for campus transit.
   </p>
   <p>
    Under the guidance of John Bartholdi, Manhattan Associates Chair of Supply Chain Management and former research director for the Supply Chain &amp; Logistics Institute, the
			  NextBuzz system earned an
			  Innovation award from the Georgia
			  Transit Association in December 2014.
   </p>
  </div>
  <!-- container breadcrumbs -->
